Concatenation
Length of a string
Substring Extraction
String Manipulation
Heredoc

Concatenation:

# Concatenate two strings
str1="Hello, "
str2="World!"
result="$str1$str2"
echo $result  
# Output: Hello, World!

Length of a string:

# Calculate the length of a string
my_string="This is a sample string"
length=${#my_string}
echo "Length of the string is $length"  
# Output: Length of the string is 23

Substring Extraction:

# Extract a substring from a string
full_string="This is a sample text"
substring="${full_string:5:6}"  # Starting at index 5, take 6 characters
echo "Substring: $substring"  
# Output: Substring: is a s

String Manipulation:

# Replace a substring in a string
original_string="I love Linux and Linux is awesome."
replaced_string="${original_string/Linux/Unix}"
echo "Replaced String: $replaced_string"  
# Output: Replaced String: I love Unix and Unix is awesome.

Heredoc (Here Document):

# Using a heredoc to define a multi-line string
cat <<EOF
This is a
multi-line
string.
EOF

cat <<EOF > output.txt
This is a
multi-line
string.
EOF


